<topic id='business_definition_observable_entity.description'>
  <title>Description</title>
  <titlealts>
    <searchtitle>NHS Business Definition: Observable Entity - Description</searchtitle>
  </titlealts>
  <body>

  <p>
An 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_observable_entity">Observable Entity</xref>
 is a 
    <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_clinical_intervention">CLINICAL INTERVENTION</xref>
.  </p>
  <p>
An 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_observable_entity">Observable Entity</xref>
 represents a question or assessment which can produce an answer or result.  </p>
  <p>For example:</p>
  <ul>
      <li>
         <div>
            <xref outputclass="element" keyref="element_systolic_blood_pressure">SYSTOLIC BLOOD PRESSURE</xref>
         </div>
      </li>
      <li>
         <p>Colour of urine</p>
      </li>
      <li>
         <p>Glomerular filtration rate.</p>
      </li>
  </ul>
  <p>
For further information on 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_observable_entity">Observable Entities</xref>
, see the see the: 
    <xref href="https://hscic.kahootz.com/gf2.ti/f/762498/30206597/PDF/-/SNOMED_CT_Hierarchy_Fact_Sheet.pdf"
            scope="external"
            format="html">SNOMED CT Fact Sheet</xref>
.  </p>

